Regarding the NJ similarities, like another Redditter has said before, ILLIT focuses on the more hyperpop and anime like sound while NJ only used this sound like once or twice. IMO it this song has "Get up" vibes but that's it. I think it just sucks that HYBE released another 5 member group (even though it was 6, but easily could've done 7) and only had 6 considering the amount of talent we saw in RUNext.
